Type: <b>Bug</b>

If I create a subAgent and inside that subAgent I don't have access to the `runSubAgent` tool anymore.

I am creating a subAgent from my main chat window and the subAgents don't have the 'agent' tool access to them. I remember creating subAgents within SubAgents with the 'runSubAgent' tool and for some reason now the tool itself is not getting listed in any subAgents and all my subAgents complain they don't know how to call the tool and how to make the 'runSubAgent' tool call and going haywire. I had to spend hours and hours of various trials and combinations only to feel like its a bug and its a serious bug of course. 

Also, I have the "Cutom Agent in Subagent" enabled. 

I used almost 10 different models including Opus 4.5, Gemini 3 flash, Gemini 3 Pro. I made almost 50+ premium requests just to test it.

**Test Setup 1 using Prompt**

1. I have a `/dispatch` prompt that takes a request and it has access to the `agent` tool - It can happily create subAgents.
2. The `/dispatch` will spawn the `dispatcher` subAgent and this is completely blocked as it doesn't have access to `agent` tool. Not just this agent, I have so many other agents that doesn't have the `agent` tool.

**Test Setup 2 using agent**

1. I am not using prompt file and now directly used the `dispatcher` agent and now it has `agent` tool in it as expected.
2. I am creating subAgent `codeSearcher` and now that has the same issue, it doesn't have access to `agent` tool too. 

I tested using the latest VS Code insiders and also one version before it also has the same issues.

