microsoft/vscode#292444.body:
## Bug

When a custom agent (`.agent.md`) specifies an array of models for fallback selection, the subagent incorrectly uses the **last** matching model instead of the **first**.

## Root Cause

In `runSubagentTool.ts`, the nested loop `break` only exits the inner loop, allowing the outer loop to continue and overwrite `modeModelId`:

```typescript
for (const qualifiedName of modeModelQualifiedNames) {
    const lmByQualifiedName = this.languageModelsService.lookupLanguageModelByQualifiedName(qualifiedName);
    for (const fullId of this.languageModelsService.getLanguageModelIds()) {
        const lmById = this.languageModelsService.lookupLanguageModel(fullId);
        if (lmById && lmById?.id === lmByQualifiedName?.id) {
            modeModelId = fullId;
            break;  // ❌ Only exits inner loop
        }
    }
}
```

## Fix

Use a labeled break to exit both loops on first match:

```typescript
outer: for (const qualifiedName of modeModelQualifiedNames) {
    const lmByQualifiedName = this.languageModelsService.lookupLanguageModelByQualifiedName(qualifiedName);
    for (const fullId of this.languageModelsService.getLanguageModelIds()) {
        const lmById = this.languageModelsService.lookupLanguageModel(fullId);
        if (lmById && lmById?.id === lmByQualifiedName?.id) {
            modeModelId = fullId;
            break outer;  // ✅ Exits both loops
        }
    }
}
```

The correct pattern already exists in `chatInputPart.ts#switchModelByQualifiedName`.

